            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3ENo%20more%20awesome%20sight%20has%20ever%20occurred%20in%20history%20than%20when%20Mount%20Sinai%20began%20to%20shake%20and%20tremble%20under%20the%20power%20of%20God.%20Paul%20records%2C%20%22Moses%20himself%20was%20so%20frightened%20at%20the%20sight%20that%20he%20said%2C%20%E2%80%98I%20am%20terrified%20and%20trembling'%20%22%20(Hebrews%2012%3A21).%20The%20entire%20mountain%20was%20covered%20with%20%22flaming%20fire%2C%20darkness%2C%20gloom%2C%20and%20whirlwind%22%20(v.%2018).%20In%20addition%2C%20all%20the%20people%20%22heard%20an%20awesome%20trumpet%20blast%20and%20a%20voice%20with%20a%20message%20so%20terrible%20that%20they%20begged%20God%20to%20stop%20speaking%22%20(v.%2019).%20This%20frightening%20demonstration%20of%20sound%20effects%20and%20raw%20power%20made%20even%20the%20bravest%20soul%20tremble%20and%20was%20intended%20to%20bring%20the%20Israelites%20to%20an%20unforgettable%20sense%20of%20reverence%20and%20godly%20fear.%20%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EPaul%20said%2C%20%22Let%20us%20be%20thankful%20and%20please%20God%20by%20worshiping%20him%20with%20holy%20fear%20and%20awe.%20For%20our%20God%20is%20a%20consuming%20fire%22%20(Hebrews%2012%3A28-29).%20In%20worship%2C%20we%20do%20not%20approach%20a%20physical%20mountain%2C%20but%20we%20come%20to%20the%20eternal%20mountain%20of%20God%3A%20Zion%2C%20%22the%20heavenly%20Jerusalem%22%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E(v.%2022).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EOne%20day%20we%20will%20stand%20before%20God%20Himself%2C%20the%20One%20who%20moves%20mountains.%20In%20the%20meantime%2C%20let%20us%20heed%20the%20words%20of%20the%20psalmist%3A%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E%22Tremble%2C%20O%20earth%2C%20at%20the%20presence%20of%20the%20Lord%2C%20at%20the%20presence%20of%20the%20God%20of%20Israel%22%20(Psalm%20114%3A7).%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
